 out. Users benefit from being able to sign on because it associates content they create with their account and allows various permissions to be set for their roles. The user module supports user roles which establish fine grained permissions allowing each role to do only what the administrator wants them to. Each user is assigned to one or more roles. By default there are two roles <em>anonymous</em> - a user who has not logged in, and <em>authenticated</em> a user who has signed up and who has been authorized.','6.28'),(2078,'modules/user/user.module:1903','default','A visitor accessing your website is assigned a unique ID, or session ID, which is stored in a cookie. The cookie does not contain personal information, but acts as a key to retrieve information from your site. Users should have cookies enabled in their web browser when using your site.','6.28'),(2079,'modules/user/user.module:1904','default','For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@user\">User module</a>.','6.28'),(2080,'modules/user/user.module:1907','default','Drupal allows users to register, login, log out, maintain user profiles, etc. Users of the site may not use their own names to post content until they have signed up for a user account.','6.28'),(2081,'modules/user/user.module:1910','default','This web page allows administrators to register new users. Users\' e-mail addresses and usernames must be unique.','6.28'),(2082,'modules/user/user.module:1912','default','Set up username and e-mail address access rules for new <em>and</em> existing accounts (currently logged in accounts will not be logged out). If a username or e-mail address for an account matches any deny rule, but not an allow rule, then the account will not be allowed to be created or to log in. A host rule is effective for every page view, not just registrations.','6.28'),(2083,'modules/user/user.module:1914','default','Permissions let you control what users can do on your site. Each user role (defined on