e when using Lightbox2 Lite.','6.28'),(7701,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Simultaneous','6.28'),(7702,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Width then height','6.28'),(7703,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Height then width','6.28'),(7704,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Resize sequence','6.28'),(7705,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','The sequence to use for the resizing animation.','6.28'),(7706,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Resize duration','6.28'),(7707,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','The duration (in seconds) of the resizing animation.  Enter a value between 0 and 10.','6.28'),(7708,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Appearance duration','6.28'),(7709,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','The duration (in seconds) of the lightbox appearance animation.  Enter a positive number less than 10.','6.28'),(7710,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Caption slide down duration','6.28'),(7711,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','The duration (in seconds) of the caption sliding-down animation.  Enter a value between 0 and 10.','6.28'),(7712,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Lightbox2 JS is a simple, unobtrusive script used to overlay images on the current page. It\'s a snap to setup and works on all modern browsers. The module comes with a Lightbox2 Lite option which does not use the JQuery libraries; it is therefore less likely to conflict with anything else.','6.28'),(7713,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Places images above your current page, not within. This frees you from the constraints of the layout, particularly column widths. Keeps users on the same page. Clicking to view an image and then having to click the back button to return to your site is bad for continuity (and no fun!).','6.28'),(7714,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general','default','Features','6.28'),(7715,'/admin/settings/lightbox2/general',